So many of you have been keeping up with what I’ve been working on last 11 days in my stories.

You’ve seen me talking about these kids and trying to raise money for them.

You’ve seen me at my absolute peak and potentially depending on when you’ve signed on… You’ve probably seen me at my lowest as well.

I didn’t know how big of a beast this would be. I didn’t know how many angels there truly were.

but I DID know one thing for sure.

I knew that you would show up for them no matter if there were 70 or 1700.

I KNEW & you did.

This box has held those angels for the last 11 days.

The forgotten ones. The teens. The babies. The siblings whose baby sister got sponsored but they didn’t.

I’ve held this box all day every single day and sat on my nightstand next to me while I tried to sleep each night.

& while I held them, I KNEW you guys were holding me.

 Every single time I started to fall apart another one of you showed up to hold me up.

We are not done yet. But we will finish this thing.

Because that’s what we do. We show up and we get it done.

No matter what. No matter how many. 

When these parents show up on Monday morning there will be a bag for their child. (I believe it.)

You built a bridge between them and a Christmas miracle.

I KNEW YOU WOULD.😭

I have so much to tell you, but I am so physically and emotionally drained I just need a rest before I do the big recap.

But for sake of time and your hearts, I have some news!!!!

This morning thousands of parents showed up to the Salvation Army to find out if anyone was listening when they humbly called out for help.

You my friend, you answered EVERY. SINGLE. CALL. 😭😭😭😭😭😭😭😭😭😭😭😭 NEARLY TWO THOUSAND.

I saw them walking in. I saw them try not to cry & I saw the promise God made to look after his people, come into life.

Sometimes we ask God why he doesn’t “do something” when there is a need…but over the last two weeks we rallied together and quietly said, “he did, he sent us.”

Thank you for loving on children & parents who will never know you to thank you.

Here’s to the truest reason for this season.

(Wish I could tag each of you🥹)

WE DID IT.🙏🏽🫶🏽😭
Everything I ever put on my list couldn’t add up to this 🤍
The Secret to having it all: perspective to see that you already do. 🤍

Reminders for a hard day:

Change is the only thing that stays the same. You’ll be ok 🫶🏽

Keep. Going.

What you focus on you attract more of, so when you notice your thoughts are low, set an intention to think of extra cheery things to be thankful for.

You were NOT meant to do this life alone. Call your friends. Call your parent, your sibling, your cousin, your aunt.

You CAN do it all, but not all at once. Or maybe you can…but even still, you shouldn’t.

Happiness > Pure Productivity 

You weren’t put here to just exist. 

When you move with purpose the water never stops rippling…not until it reaches the shore.

Someone needs you to show up.
Someone needs you to embrace your story.
Someone needs YOUR light.
Your hug.
Your encouragement.
Your kind smile.
Your love.

Someone is you.***
Although I know for a fact there are others out there who do too.

Keep going.
Keep going.
This life is going to be a GOOD GOOD STORY.

No more excuses - none.

You were meant to do something specific. There’s a unique purpose/dream(most likely a few) all the way down in your heart.

A way you can uniquely serve and show up and make an impact while you’re here - promise it’s true.

 Now, let me ask you a question…if you let the world keep you from committing to your dream, do you think God’s just gonna let his mission die along with your motivation?

No. He wants the thing he placed in your heart FOR YOU - that’s why it’s there!!

But if you choose not to use it…
If you don’t get out of your own way and just do it - he will find someone who will.

People have been praying for the thing you’ve been feeling the urge to do.

He’s set a plan in motion.
He’s trying to send you.

It is never too late to change your mind. 🫶🏽

I pretended to be in college for a WHILE after I dropped (ok failed) out.

The shame I felt over changing my mind about the future was uh…overwhelming to say the least.

My fear of telling my family that I wouldn’t be the first ever to graduate from college was indescribable - but my fear of regret over not at-least giving my dream a try was bigger.

I wish I could tell my daughter that I actually got a degree, (and in retrospect a business degree would’ve been smart) but at-least I can say, “your mama failed forward and followed her dream, even when things got really hard.”

It’s never too late.
There is no amount of time that would be deemed “wasted” long enough to be worth you staying in a career if it doesn’t feel like home.

Anyone else ever felt ashamed or afraid to tell someone when you’ve changed your mind? 🥴

Love you. 🫶🏽

2022 was a B. A bear. A beast. A regular ol’ biatch.

Growing pains in business and in life, placed perfectly on top of a crazy experience with a short term employee (no you probably don’t know her, she was only here a few months) who was robbing us blind and stole just about every nice thing I’ve ever owned. (Insert security footage - grab the 🍿jk) all while feeling low & desperate to support people I love going through indescribably hard seasons…

Yeah, it was a lot.

 I turned myself inside out without realizing it.

I stepped away from social media for nearly 3 months (outside of sharing things I needed to for work).

I didn’t feel hopeful. I didn’t feel strong. I didn’t feel capable.

I didn’t feel like I was making a damn bit of difference.

I watched the ground around me drying up in every part of my life. 
(Besides my marriage but that’s bc I married a saint)

All I could see was a drought but the water I felt desperate for was hope.

It was obviously time for a change, so I did what I do.

I pulled my *now loose fitting* big girl pants up, grabbed a watering can & got to work.

Each time I poured out a bit in an effort to serve, I felt a little less like a dried up desert myself.

The weeks went on and one day Matt text me to say I seemed different.

Then this week my friends Claire and Amanda said I looked different, I think the word they used was actually STRONG!

I looked in the mirror and they snapped these photos to show me what they were seeing…

A poppy pushing up through broken soil.

Reminder: we all have our “glam lash days” and our “Id really just like to not throw up in this car,” days.

& We’re equally ridiculous and lovable on both.

#loveyoutoo #selflove #youarebeautiful

It was never about the pictures…

When I was 19 I didn’t know how to run a business. I didn’t know how to make $ or market or price or even how to shoot really…

But I knew my why.

I wanted to make an impact. I wanted to get my arms around as many girls as I possibly could.

I knew this:  when people outside of our daily lives sprinkle even the tiniest seeds of goodness and encouragement  over us, they land in the cracks of our insecurities and sometimes, really beautiful things start to grow.

This week I took headshots for 88 girls/women. 88 times I got to shoot them a smile, give them a tiny affirmation, nod and say they did great or compliment something I genuinely loved about them.

I do a lot of different things in my professional life, but they all lead back to my ONE thing…

Reminding girls in every stage of life, that they deserve to shine.

If you wanna find the way, find your why.

Thanks so much for having me @jaofthebluegrass

We’re all heading in a different direction racing 100 miles an hour…but most don’t truly realize, you get farther by focusing your direction and keeping your sights set, taking one small calculated step at a time.

It’s the micro moves. The little but intentional things that make the difference. The email to check in. The sweet messages to clients. The goal setting that truly only takes a couple hours. The website updates. The hashtags. The one foot in front of the other to keep yourself on the ever narrowing path to that life you want to live.

Don’t focus on calendars. Focus on steps. Focus on YOUR FOCUS.

Slow and steady, babe.

⚠️Trigger warning ⚠️ 

Shame, Fear & regret will build a house around you with walls {almost} too high to climb.

There’s no windows to keep you from feeling the sunlight on your face or looking off into the distance for hope.

No doors, to make it seem like you can never leave.

There are holes in the roof, so the dark clouds can be easily seen and the rain falls at an awkward pace as a reminder of the “things you’ve done to put yourself here.” {lie}

If you live here now {hey my once roomie} there’s something you may not have noticed before… shh, I found a hatch in the floor.

It’s under a dusty rug over there and yeah, it looks HEAVY - but don’t be scared.

If you’re willing to try, you’ll find just enough strength to pull it up, so look inside.

A crawl space!

Don’t get me wrong, the crawl space is tight.

It’s dark and once you start going it can be a little disorienting if you look behind…

But if you just keep moving, there’s an exit there. Swear.

You can leave this place, have hope again and breathe fresh air.

Friend…let yourself believe it when you read this again. 
There is not ONE thing you’ve done before that makes you unworthy of living and being truly happy again.

Love you. Love yourself.

Don’t tell me you’ve never had one of those HOLY HELLO to-do list days.

“The way you want to be, is the way you are.”-Myla Malicote

When Myla said this it didn’t make sense to me at first.

But she’s unusually wise, so I sat and thought on what she said and how literal she is.

The way you want to be, is the way you are…

The way you are is the way you want to be

You choose to stay the same even when *say*you want more. OUCH

You must truly want to stay the way that you are. Otherwise you’d change. 🥵

By not growing you’re saying you choose the pain of staying the same over the discomfort of growth. 🫣

It hits different each time I try to break it down further.

So, tonight I’m remembering that I am exactly who I choose to be right now *no matter what my words might say*…and tomorrow I’m going to choose better.

For myself and for her.

Don’t forget to check yourself every now and then friends. It’s much easier to talk than it is to move.

But like Myla said…you become what you choose.

Just bloom.

Not because someone else is.
Not because you need to.
Not because the world says you’re running out of time.

Bloom for you.

I am so ridiculously grateful for the change of pace that’s upon us!

Minus the mountain of editing we’re about to take on 😅😅😅 and the schedule next week 😆 and that other cabin we’re renovating right now 🏠 and summer weddings and new brand clients, but otherwise!!!

Ok ok, it’s still a lot BUT I’m slowing down in my own ways and we’re living for it over here!

I don’t deserve my day to day but I can tell ya, no one is more grateful for what and who they have than I am. 🤍

I’ve been very fortunate to have built something (a few things actually 🥹) that I’m very proud of.

On occasion someone will ask me *how* it happened. How I keep pace. How I decide which chances to take. How I make the right moves in business (which I don’t always make)

But the honest truth is, I don’t know how.

Full transparency…
I don’t usually assess how before I decide to make a move, small or life altering.😬🫣

When I’m staring down a decision, here’s my process…

First I go to my gut, my God & my guy.

I ask myself why I want to do something. Is it purely selfish or is it for a greater good?

I try to give a solid answer on why it’s a good move for our family.

Then I ask why it’s important for ME to be the one who does it.

Add a quick ponder over if this will give me the chance to shed some light or not and…✨

If it checks the boxes, gets a good gut response, has support from Matt and feels like God’s in it, it’s a resounding yes from me.

The how ALWAYS sorts itself out after that.

***The times it hasn’t have all been because I chose to act on something without truly checking my ego and my heart.***

Sure, I’m always scared but not because im worried I won’t figure out HOW.

I’m scared because I know who loses if I don’t win. It’s not just her, but she’s more than enough motivation to make me refuse to give in.

How can’t be the only question. Why is the true way to get yourself a win.

I don’t know who needs to hear this but,
It is ok to find yourself again now.

I know, most of you will say,”I’m not choosing to be here,” but often times, I think we fall into the shame spiral and subconsciously believe it would be better for us to stay down after a hard thing, stay hidden after failing, being embarrassed or ashamed, to stay simple or quiet or convenient to be around.

But hey, maybe it’s time. You deserve to find her. The most you-y version of the girl you see in the mirror.

You need her. The WORLD needs her.

 #youbeyou #youdeserveit #selflove

My worry didn’t give me peace…And neither does my self talk when parenting is involved.

I’ll never be done trying to get it right. I’m ready to stop being the guilt collector and instead be the one collecting time.

I could be enjoying her while she falls asleep, but on occasion I spend a good part of that time worrying.

Mama, if your guilt hangs heavy around your neck, I can’t give you a word of advice…but you’re not alone.🫠

& when (please not if) I find a way to overcome it, Ill come back and let you know exactly how I’ve done it.

Ever gone to sit down somewhere and the seat was far below where you thought it would be?

For a second there you’re falling, you quickly question if the seat was pulled out from under you, or if your eyes deceived you before you sat… but even in the falling you HOPE you’re about to land.

That’s the exact way I’d describe the last year of my life.

Every time I sat, I fell. Everytime I took a step, I was juuuuust short.

I was looking but NOT SEEING.
Asking but not listening.
Working but not resting. Ever.

I just knew I was so close to landing on something solid…I HOPED. I just wasn’t sure if I’d land on my feet or my face.

I ran myself to the edge of burnout and then this summer, I decided to do it all.
I saw , I listened, I rested.

Id like to say it was glorious, but a lot of it was uncomfortable…& still is.

Growing pains, right?!

But I’m feeling the tightness in my chest fade.
I’m hearing truth about my own goodness and not just stories of shame I’ve created for myself.
I’m finding support and people who truly want to help us grow.

I’m finally feeling good about the falling in between.

Ps. I’ve been doing a lot, but i think little things add up.

I’ve been doing a course in self esteem, got my hormones and levels in check (thank you Lord for @solutionsivvitaminbar ), started shifting my schedule to reflect my priorities and began focusing on actually getting sleep.

I truly feel myself coming back to life and it’s only been weeks.

Prioritize your health, don’t be like this girl & wait until you’re in a complete pretzel to ask for your turn. You deserve to feel good and fully live life. BE THE PRIORITY. It’s time.

She had dimples in her butt and joy in her heart. 🤍 

That second part makes the first feel less like it matters.

⚠️ possible trigger warning ⚠️ 
My senior year I couldn’t control a whole lot. I FELT like I couldn’t anyway.

I was anxious and worried. I feared I wasn’t smart enough to go to college. Couldn’t focus enough to hack it even if I did get in.

I felt I wasn’t desirable enough for someone to want to marry. Wasn’t tall enough. Wasn’t outgoing enough. Not confident enough. Not connected enough to have the chance to chase a dream.

I felt out of control so I took unhealthy control over what I ate. Like, “ok Kels, there’s 12 calories in that saltine.” 😩

I landed at less than 100lbs just before senior spring break in Panama City Beach. 

I remember thinking, “If I’m about to go down in flames, I’ll at least burn HOT.” But I didn’t. I fizzled out. Smothered my own light in the pursuit of what I thought someone else might want me to be.

Spoiler alert 🚨 It didn’t work out. If I wanted it then, I don’t have it now. (But I got something much better once I figured it out)

It took time, a whole lot of prayer and one really incredible guy to break my unhealthy relationship with the “happiness equation” I’d created in my mind.

Turns out, joy makes space for imperfections like dimples in your bum. 

And I’ve found that if we let it, love can replace our need for total control with letting go.

I love this body. I love the life it carries me through.

But WHY!!!!!!??????!
